rdt.title: Deep-tree search
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

! What it does

By default the search input filters the ''current stage's'' visible rows only and matches against each row's ''name'' and ''hint''. Two new pill strips widen this on two independent axes:

* ''Reach'' (teal) — WHERE in the cascade tree to search. Default: local (current stage only).
* ''Search-in'' (violet) — WHICH fields the matcher reads. Default: per-row `ca-search-fields`, falling back to global default `name hint`.

Both strips use the same push / remove / DEL / navigate grammar as the existing Filter and Visibility strips. Strips appear only when at least one pill is pushed; hidden otherwise.

! Reach strip — WHERE to search

|!Pill |!Leader |!Effect |
|🔍 Here |`d` |Walk every reachable drill under the currently-visible stage. |
|🌐 Everywhere |`g` |Walk every reachable drill under the active view's root. The drill stack stays put — the pill widens the search frontier, it doesn't move you. |

The two Reach pills are ''mutually exclusive'' — pushing one evicts the other. Only one scope is ever active. DEL on the focused pill removes it (returning to local search).

When a Reach pill is active, results carry a breadcrumb prefix (`Kinds → Task → fields  priority: enum`) naming the drill chain from the search anchor to the matched row.

! Search-in strip — WHICH fields to read

|!Pill |!Field key |!Source |!Visible inline? |
|🏷 Name |`name` |cascade item |Yes — the row's title. Inline match highlight. |
|💡 Hint |`hint` |cascade item |Yes — the row's subtitle / tooltip. Inline match highlight. |
|📝 Description |`description` |cascade item |No — `ca-description`. Match surfaces as a snippet line below the row. |
|↪ Aliases |`aliases` |cascade item |No — `ca-aliases` (alternate names / synonyms). Snippet. |
|🔎 Search-text |`searchText` |cascade item |No — `ca-search-text` (catch-all bag). Snippet. |
|📄 Text |`text` |''tiddler field'' |No — the backing tiddler's body. Snippet. |

Multiple Search-in pills can coexist. When any are active, the matcher reads the UNION of those fields, ignoring per-row config and global default. No Search-in pills active = matcher uses each row's `ca-search-fields` declaration, falling back to the global config at ''`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/search-fields-default`'' (ships `name hint`).

''Leader `a`'' pushes all six shipped Search-in pills at once — equivalent to "match anywhere".

! Adding your own Search-in pills

The matcher's field-resolver walks ''two layers'' per field key:

# ''Cascade-item property'' — `item.<key>` (read at item-build time from `ca-<key>` on entries / actions / synthetic items).
# ''Tiddler-field fallback'' — when step 1 produces nothing AND the row has a backing tiddler, `wiki.getTiddler(item.title).fields[<key>]` is consulted.

That second layer is what makes the shipped ''📄 Text'' pill work without protocol changes — `text` is a tiddler field, not a cascade-item property. The same fallback applies to ANY tiddler field. To expose `tags` (or `caption`, `modifier`, `modified`, an author-defined field, …) as a Search-in pill, ship a tiddler:

```
title: $:/plugins/example/field/tags
tags: $:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/field
ca-field-name: tags
ca-field-chip: 🏷 Tags
ca-field-hint: Match against the tiddler's tags field.
```

Array-typed fields (`tags`, list-fields) are flattened to space-separated strings before substring matching, so `tags: work urgent` matches a query of `urgen`.

! Multi-match visualization

When a row matches in multiple fields (e.g. `name` AND `description`), each match contributes:

* Inline highlight on the visible name / hint slot (whichever matched).
* One snippet line per non-displayed match (description / aliases / searchText / author-declared), shown beneath the row with the matched field name + 24 chars of context before + the matched substring (highlighted) + 40 chars after.

So a single row can carry inline highlight AND multiple snippets — the user sees every reason the row is in the result list.

! Picking a deep result — three gestures

When a Reach pill is active, results carry a `_path` array (the drill chain from the anchor). Picking a result replays the path so the cascade lands at the row's natural parent. Three gestures distinguish what happens next:

|!Gesture |!Effect |
|''Enter'' |Replay path + execute (fire leaves, drill into drills). |
|''Right-arrow'' |Replay path + drill (no-op on plain leaves). |
|''Space'' |''Pin only'' — replay path, select the row at its natural stage, but do NOT fire / edit / open the action menu. Safe inspection gesture for destructive matches. |

Any `<<parent-picked>>` / `<<stage-N-picked>>` context the row's actions depend on resolves the same way as a manual drill.

! Authoring searchable text on cascade items

Beyond exposing tiddler fields via pills (above), each cascade item can also declare its OWN searchable strings — useful for synthetic items (no backing tiddler) and for adding searchable content without polluting tiddler fields:

```
ca-description: Longer-form explanation, not normally rendered.
ca-aliases: locate search lookup synonym
ca-search-text: catch-all bag for body / keywords / hidden text
ca-search-fields: name hint description aliases    (per-row override)
ca-search-skip: yes                                 (exclude from deep walk)
```

''`ca-search-skip: yes`'' opts a row out of deep search results AND prevents its subtree from being descended. Useful for `+ Add new` input prompts whose name only makes sense in their immediate context. Default auto-skip applies to `text`, `number`, `date`, `toggle`, and `confirm` row kinds.

! Caps

The walk is bounded — no walk is ever unbounded — by three hard caps (config tiddler defaults):

|!Config |!Default |!What it does |
|`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/deep-search-max-depth` |4 |Maximum drill depth from the search anchor |
|`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/deep-search-max-nodes` |800 |Total items visited before the walk aborts |
|`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/deep-search-max-ms` |80 |Wall-clock time per keystroke before the walk aborts |

When any cap fires, the result list ends with a ''truncation hint row'' so you know to refine the query.

! Sending the messages programmatically

A toolbar button, sidebar item, or any external wikitext can push pills via the same widget messages the leaders use:

```
<$action-sendmessage $message="rimir-cascade-palette-add-reach"
  reach="$:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/reach/here"/>

<$action-sendmessage $message="rimir-cascade-palette-add-field"
  field="$:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/field/text"/>
```

`rimir-cascade-palette-reset-reach` / `-reset-fields` clear the strips.

! Limitations (MVP)

* Action menus are not walked. Search lists the entity rows themselves; drilling into an action menu is a separate gesture.
* No per-keystroke memo cache yet — each keystroke recomputes the walk. Caps keep this fast on real-world trees.
* Result ranking is BFS-natural (shallower matches first; same-depth keeps cascade's sort). Exact-match boost and other ranking are on the roadmap.
* Pills don't persist across sessions or get saved into Presets yet — they're session-local. Preset integration is on the roadmap.
* No ''+ Add Reach / + Add Field'' picker pill yet (à la Presets' `+` save pill) — pills are pushed only via leaders or external messages for now.
